<!--
	**
	** This Maven2 build file is the preferred way to build JQuantLib
	**
	** There are 4 main profiles:
	**
	**     * quick (default)
	**         Intended to run everytime a new commit happens and/or relatively short periods of time.
	**         - no javadoc generation
	**         - no unit tests
	**         - no integration tests: no surefire reports; no cobertura reports
	**         - no site generation/deployment
    **         $ mvn clean package
	**
	**     * nightly
	**         Intended to run once a day, producing documentation but skipping test coverage reports.
    **         - generates javadocs
    **         - no integration tests: no surefire reports; no cobertura reports
	**         - generates and deploys site
    **         $ mvn clean site-deploy
	**
	**     * weekly
	**         Intended to generate full documentation.
    **         - generates javadocs
    **         - runs integration tests: surefire reports and cobertura reports are generated
    **         - generates and deploys site
    **         $ mvn clean site-deploy
	**
	**     * release-profile (based on Super POM at http://maven.apache.org/pom.html#The_Super_POM )
	**         Intended to generate full documentation and tag a new release.
	**         - activated via command line option
    **         - generates javadocs
    **         - runs integration tests: surefire reports and cobertura reports are generated
	**         - deploys artifacts
	**         - deploys documentation
    **         $ mvn clean deploy site-deploy -DperformRelease=true
	**
	** @author Richard Gomes
	**
-->

